  		<div><h3>Comments</h3></div>
  		<div>
  			<div id="item-4322"><p>Ah, Rebecca&#8230;a recipe for fudge sauce&#8230;I was just looking for one to go with some homemade ice cream! It seemed wrong, somehow, to pour something hershey-ish on it. And I don&#8217;t need to go out to buy anything-I&#8217;ve got it all here-thank you!</p></div>
  			<div class="date byline">
  				
  				<a href="http://lindystoast.com"><span class="alias">lindy</span></a>
  				<span>on September 8, 2007</span>
  			</div>
  		</div><div>
  			<div id="item-4326"><p>Why has this steamy weather returned to bother our cooking anyway.  I love cooking pasta in advance and serving it cold and for some reason I forgot to do that this summer. It is definitely a good way to have a relaxing meal. Usually I am cooking til the last minute. That chocolate sauce does sound good. Maybe I will try it with less sugar.</p></div>
  			<div class="date byline">
  				
  				<a href="http://www.izzyeats.blogspot.com"><span class="alias">izzy&#039;s mama</span></a>
  				<span>on September 8, 2007</span>
  			</div>
  		</div><div>
  			<div id="item-4332"><p>My grandmother used to make a chocolate sauce that my family has been trying to recreate for years. I know it had all those ingredients in it (except possibly the vanilla). I&#8217;m wondering if this is the same. I&#8217;ll have to do a test run for my parents next time I see them.</p></div>
  			<div class="date byline">
  				
  				<a href="http://kitchenography.typepad.com"><span class="alias">Julie</span></a>
  				<span>on September 10, 2007</span>
  			</div>
  		</div><div>
  			<div id="item-4335"><p>Actually, Julie, the vanilla is my own addition.</p>
<p>Lindy, you&#8217;ll have to let me know how you like it!</p>
<p>Hi, izzy&#8217;s mama! I can relate to your desire to use less sugar, but sometimes these cooked sugar things are calculated proportionally and might not come out right if you mess with them. It might be better just to put less sauce on your ice cream&#8230;</p></div>
